# UI Package (Shared Components) Rules

## Architecture
- Shared UI component library
- Built with React + TypeScript
- Styled with Tailwind CSS
- Storybook for component documentation

## Development Commands
```bash
pnpm dev         # Start Storybook development server
pnpm build       # Build the package
pnpm lint        # Lint the code
pnpm check:types # Type check
pnpm test        # Run tests
pnpm ui          # Storybook shortcut command
```

## Component Development
- Use shadcn/ui as base components
- Extend components with proper variants
- Use cva (class-variance-authority) for variants
- Export components from index files
- Follow existing component patterns

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS exclusively
- Use CSS variables from `shadcn-theme.css`
- Create proper variant classes
- Follow responsive design principles
- Use semantic color tokens

## Component Structure
- Create stories for all components
- Include proper TypeScript types
- Add JSDoc documentation
- Use proper prop interfaces
- Export variants separately when needed

## Form Components
- Use react-hook-form integration
- Create field wrapper components
- Implement proper validation patterns
- Follow form-builder conventions

## Layout Components
- Create reusable layout patterns
- Support responsive behavior
- Use proper semantic HTML
- Follow accessibility guidelines

## Data Components
- Create table/grid components
- Support sorting and filtering
- Implement proper pagination
- Use virtualization for large datasets

## Hooks & Utilities
- Create reusable custom hooks
- Export utility functions
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Follow React hook conventions

## Storybook
- Create stories for all components
- Include multiple variants
- Add proper controls
- Document component usage
- Include accessibility checks

## Testing
- Test component behavior
- Test accessibility features
- Use React Testing Library
- Mock external dependencies
- Maintain test coverage

## Theme & Theming
- Use CSS custom properties
- Support light/dark modes
- Follow design system tokens
- Maintain consistency across components